<biogHist>
<abstract>The Adoption of Children Act Amendment Act 1945 (Act no. 1945/031 (9 &amp; 10 Geo. VI No.31)) commenced on 30 January 1946. The amendments came into force on 30 January 1946 and amended Rules operated from 24 October 1930.</abstract>
<p>The Adoption of Children Act Amendment Act restricted access to the original birth certificate of adopted children in two new ways:</p>
<list><item>a person who was born in WA but adopted in another Australian State or Territory could not access their original WA birth certificate</item>
<item>a person who was born in another Australian State or Territory but who was adopted in WA could not access their original birth certificate</item></list>
<p>These records could be released with the written permission of the Registrar General, but in practice this was rare.</p>

</biogHist>
